HOM3init - NOTICE
=================

This repository contains ONLY the boot + init layer of the HOM3 sovereign OS:

  - hom3init  : the PID 1 boot sequence and process supervisor
  - hom3recovery : the native first-boot / recovery console
  - the raw syscall FFI layer it uses

It intentionally DOES NOT contain:

  - hom3node : the chain / keystore / signing workload (Ed25519, Argon2,
    canonicalization, the append-only logbook). This is where key generation
    and custody actually happen.
  - The provenance / attestation method (an external-witness provenance scheme
    and an externally-anchored signed logbook) - the subject of a pending U.S.
    provisional patent application. This method is NOT named or disclosed here.
  - The board bring-up firmware (Rockchip DDR init blob, ARM Trusted Firmware /
    BL31, U-Boot). Those are third-party and sit below the sovereignty line.

Patent posture
--------------
A provisional patent application covers certain provenance/attestation methods
used elsewhere in the HOM3 system. Nothing in THIS repository practices or
discloses those claims:
the custody policy consulted at preflight is abstracted behind the `Sovereignty`
trait (see src/boot.rs), and the reference implementation enforces no custody
model. Publishing this component does not dedicate those separate methods to the
public.

